Reasoning: The paper deals with a learning task and presents an instance optimal learning algorithm, which suggests that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the estimation of the expected number of distinct elements, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper's focus on de-noising the empirical distribution and not relying on prior assumptions could also suggest artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the practical relevance of the paper's approach to genomics suggests that it could also belong to the statistics (cs.ST) sub-category.
